ask_language:
A <b>language</b> refers to a set of strings composed of symbols from a given alphabet. 
Example: 

A language that can take all possible strings of length 2 over the alphabet ∑ = {a, b} is L = { aa, ab, ba, bb }

The language L accepted by automaton(DFA/NDFA) can be represented as {S | S ∈ ∑* and δ*(q0, S) ∈ F} 

The language L' not accepted by automaton(DFA/NDFA) can be represented as {S | S ∈ ∑* and δ*(q0, S) ∉ F}

ask_regex:
A <b>regular expression</b> defines a search pattern. Examples of RE: 
 - (0 + 10*) : L = { 0, 1, 10, 100, 1000, 10000, … } 
 -(0*10*) : L = {ε, 0, 1, 01} 
 -(aa)*(bb)*b : L = {b, aab, aabbb, aabbbbb, aaaab, aaaabbb, …………..} (any string with an even number of a's followed by an odd number of b's)
